runs.comm: drifting down leg, glanced to short fine leg
shortish on the hips, pull and a miss
dropped short and down leg, pulled in the air... does not carry to short fine leg
Soumya dances out and lofts it to long-on, on the bounce
leading edge, spooned in front of cover as Kayes does not get hold of the flick
Chisoro strikes in the first over. Tossed up, Chisoro sneaks through the gate and timbahh! Kayes targetted the leg side again, but did not connect. The leg stump is knocked back
gentle leg-stump half-volley, Soumya picks it up and goes over midwicket. Top wristwork

encore, well not quite! Back of a length on middle, picked up over midwicket. Sibanda slides in the deep at the edge of the boundary, and swats the ball back into play. Denies Soumya back-to-back fours
yorker, dug out to leg
leg-side wide
full and angled away outside off, driven to mid-off
glanced from a leg-stump line to fine leg
another lovely pick-up shot. Shortish, hit over midwicket again
hint of slow turn outside off, worked to the leg side
slog-sweep and a miss outside off
Soumya shuffles outside leg, dabs a cut to short third man
Sabbir steps out, does not meet the pitch. Takes it on the pad, and hares across to the other end. The throw from Raza pings the keeper's thigh
loose ball down leg, picked up and flicked over backward square leg
Soumya uses his feet now, and does not meet the pitch. Deflected behind square off the thigh
sliding down the leg side, poor line. Glanced easily to the right of short fine leg
back of a length and outside off, Sabbir bangs it down the ground, flat-batted away to the long-on fence
full and outside off, Sabbir wants to attack again. He goes low for a sweep and ends up sending an edge spiralling over short third man
whipped through midwicket
away-cutter outside off, sticks in the pitch and beats Soumya
down the track, might have been another slower ball. Dragged to midwicket off the toe end of the bat
short and just outside leg, pull and a miss. May have flicked the thigh/glove. Another slower one?
short, hurries on, Sabbir toe-ends a pull to mid-off
Sabbir connects well now. Dug in outside off, he takes it from there, and pulls to midwicket boundary
low full toss, hoicked away to the wide long-on boundary
Vitori sucks pace off this bouncer, Sabbir is tricked into pulling it. He is hit on the grille of the helmet
Sabbir drives this full ball from outside off to long-on
width outside off, Sabbir flays it in the air... It flies to the right of the diving Hamilton at cover
Sabbir steps across off, looks like a slower short ball. He waits for it to arrive and middles a pull, dismissing it to the midwicket boundary. Sabbir punches gloves with Soumya
overpitched and outside off, uppish drive, but between the covers and mid-off. Make that three fours on the bounce
slower ball outside off, drilled straight to Hamilton at cover now
extra bounce on this cutter outside off, dab and a miss
full on off, tickled to short fine leg
Mutumbami misses a stumping! Williams lobs this up, Soumya dances out, does not lay bat onto it. It almost went through the keeper
chopped to point on the back foot
the man at midwicket dives full length to his right but can't stick onto the catch. Down the track and hit hard to Sibanda
Soumya dances out and lifts it straight down the ground. Creamed for a six
down the pitch and dragged behind square off an inside edge
fired outside off, Sabbir cuts in the gap between the two men behind square on the off side. A+ for placement
looped up, blocked back to the bowler
reverse-sweep and a miss outside off
flighted and rips away outside off, swish and a miss to a googly
poked to short third man
slapped off the back foot to deep cover

Hamilton just about hangs onto this skied hit. Cremer brings Soumya out of the crease with a topspinner. He makes a mess of the slog sweep, Hamilton seemed to have lost the ball, before settling under it at midwicket. Soumya tosses away a bright start
drifts in, and turns, worked in front of square on the back foot
drifting down leg, swept to short fine leg
gently knocked through midwicket
the debutant targets the leg side, but this one grips in the pitch and foils the shot. Leading edge drops in front of cover
short, skids off the surface, mistimed pull to long-on
turn again for Williams, prodded past cover
flighted on off, bunted to long-on
down the track and quietly pushed to cover for one
legbreak outside off, guided to short third man
loopier on off, defended onto the pitch even as the debutant topples over
length ball on middle, Mosaddek reverse-slaps it powerfully over backward point. Where did that come from?
tossed up legbreak, helped to short third man with soft hands. Follows up the big hit with a deft one
drifts in, blocked back to the bowler
dangled up outside off, dabbed to short third man
Sabbir steps out to the free-hit and smears it over cover
darted in, defended back to the bowler
nudged through midwicket from a middle-stump line
fired on middle, whipped through midwicket for a couple. Good urgency
flat on off, Sabbir goes low and nails a slog-sweep to the midwicket boundary. He raises his bat and acknowledges his fifty
pushed on the pads, tapped through midwicket

filthy half-tracker from round the stumps, it results in a wicket. Raza claps his hands and takes it. Darted short and down leg, Sabbir pulls well but finds the man at the edge of the boundary at backward square leg. Muzarabani completes a tumbling catch
slides on outside off, pushed to point
flighted on middle, defended
drilled through the covers as this was full and outside off
leg-side wide
drifting down leg, brushed off the pad behind square
hint of width outside off, slower through the air. Cut to deep cover on the back foot
slides on middle, Shakib drops it defensively in front of square on the off side
full on middle, Shakib manufactures room by backing away. Slapped through point
fired full on middle, drilled to cover, diving save
the debutant makes room now and chops to cover
Shakib backs away again, Chisoro is smart enough to follow the moving batsman. Poked into the covers
short on middle from round the stumps, swivel-pulled away in front of square
Shakib backs away again, he is followed again. Driven to mid-off
Shakib steps away outside leg yet again, this is tossed up well outside off. Cut and a miss
down the track and hit over the bowler's head, to long-off

bowled'em! The scoreboard pressure tells on the debutant. This was tossed up on middle, Mosaddek goes for a reverse-sweep behind square. The ball hits the inside part of his glove and disturbs the stumps. Raza is doing a good job for his side
full on the stumps, Mahmudullah steps out right away, and drags it behind square leg off an inside edge. Raza has his hands on his head

Shakib hits it into the lap of long-on. Another rank bad ball, another wicket. Half-tracker outside off, Shakib pulls it to Waller. Shakib should have packed more power in that shot. Big blow for the hosts
flat legbreak outside off, swatted to long-on
dropped short on middle, rocked back and pulled to cow corner
short legbreak outside off, Mahmudullah goes over the covers

Flighted on off, turns away a bit as well. Mahmudullah steps out and skies it. Mutumbami, who had missed a stumping earlier, keeps his cool this time and steadies himself under this (mis)hit.  Mahmudullah goes and with it Bangladesh's chances
dug in outside off, pulled to wide long-on. A fumble allows the second
full on middle, clipped through midwicket
chopped to backward point as this was faster
darted outside off, slapped to sweeper cover
flighted on middle, he goes low and scoops it in the air, over the keeper. It drops into no-man's land between short third man and short fine leg. Good placement?
pushed back to the bowler
hacked over the covers
looped up on a fourth-stump line, defended
speared full, drilled down to long-on
Cremer lands this just outside off and gets it to turn away. Fizzing legbreak. Left alone
drifts onto the leg stump, paddled to short fine leg. Another dot
legbreak outside off, sweep and a miss
slides on off, chopped to short third man
full on middle and leg, lap-scooped over the keeper
yorker, right in the blockhole on off and middle, angled to backward point
yorker on off again, dug out towards point
low full toss outside off, Nurul scoops fine on the off side now for four. Short third man had no chance
full, slower ball outside off. Dragged down the ground
cutter outside off, play and miss
short, slower ball on middle. Slogged in the gap between deep midwicket and long-on
full, another slower ball outside off. Pasted over the covers. Nurul manufactures his own pace
leg-side wide
full, another slower ball. Poked towards point
Nurul walks down the track and lofts it to long-on
leg-breakish slower ball outside off, the batsman waits and swings it over long-off
Vitori brings out another slower ball of his own. The batsman shuffles across off and misses the scoop. Mutumbami is beaten as well
Nurul steps out, picks it off his thigh, and flicks it past short fine leg for four
full and outside off, carved to sweeper cover
full on middle, Ali backs away and lashes it to cover
low full toss on off, this is sliced away behind point, beats the two men behind square
blockhole ball on off, hit to long-off. Zimbabwe stay alive in the series
